
=================
uplug-treetagger
=================

This package includes configuration files for running TreeTagger from Uplug

Supported languages are:
German, English, Spanish, French, Italian, Dutch
(see share/systems/pre)


INSTALLATION
------------

download TreeTagger models and tools from
http://www.ims.uni-stuttgart.de/projekte/corplex/TreeTagger/DecisionTreeTagger.html

Put the tagger-models and abbreviation files in
    share/ext/tree-tagger/lib/
TreeTagger binaries (tree-tagger, separate-punctuation) in
    share/ext/tree-tagger/bin/
TreeTagger scripts (lookup.perl, tokenize.pl, ...)
    share/ext/tree-tagger/cmd/


* If you run Uplug in a local directory (without explicitly installing):
  Copy the share-directory to your local Uplug location
       cp -R uplug-treetagger/share /path/to/uplug/home/dir/

* otherwise run the usual installation steps
  perl Makefile.PL
  make
  sudo make install


